\startchapter[title={About \type{appearance.el}}]

The file \type{appearance.el} is a lightweight configuration module for \type{context-lmtx-mode}
that is responsible for simple \italic{UI tweaks} and optional theme loading in Emacs.  
It focuses on adjusting common interface settings such as scroll bar width and tab spacing, 
and optionally loading a preferred color theme.

\startsection[title={Purpose}]

The main goal of \type{appearance.el} is to:
\startitemize
\item Provide basic interface customization without affecting functionality.
\item Centralize all UI-related tweaks in one place for easy maintenance.
\item Allow the user to optionally load a theme.
\stopitemize

\stopsection % Purpose

\startsection[title={Configuration Details}]

\startsubsection[title={Scroll Bar Width}]
The configuration sets:
\starttyping
(setq-default scroll-bar-width 7)
\stoptyping
This adjusts the width of the scroll bar to \bold{7 pixels} 
(for a slimmer and less intrusive appearance).

\stopsubsection

\startsubsection[title={Tab Width}]
The configuration also sets:
\starttyping
(setq-default tab-width 4)
\stoptyping
This defines the default tab character width in Emacs buffers as \bold{4 spaces}, 
which is a common convention for code indentation.

\stopsubsection

\stopsection % Configuration Details

\startsection[title={Theme Configuration (Optional)}]

An optional example theme configuration is included, using \type{dracula-theme}:

\starttyping
;;(use-package dracula-theme
;;  :ensure t
;;  :config
;;  (load-theme 'dracula t))
\stoptyping

\startitemize
\item The lines are commented out by default.
\item If uncommented, Emacs will install and activate the Dracula theme, a popular dark color scheme.
\item Uses \type{use-package} for clean package management and configuration.
\stopitemize

\stopsection % Theme Configuration

\startsection[title={Integration}]

This file ends with:
\starttyping
(provide 'appearance)
\stoptyping
This makes the module available for \type{require} in other configuration files,  
keeping the UI tweaks logically separated from functional modules.

\stopsection % Integration

\stopchapter % About appearance.el
